Title: b'Less Than Zero'
Author: Stuart J. Murphy, Frank Remkiewicz
Raw description: This story follows Perry the Penguin, who needs 9 clams to buy an ice scooter but struggles with saving money. As Perry earns, spends, finds, and even borrows clams, a simple line graph is used to introduce and explain the mathematical concept of negative numbers.

Title: b'Women and Autoimmune Disease (The Mysterious Ways Your Body Betrays Itself)'
Author: Robert G. Lahita
Raw description: A cutting-edge examination of autoimmune diseases, which disproportionately affect women. World-class immunologist Dr. Robert Lahita uses case studies to reveal early warning signs, symptoms, diagnostic processes, and innovative treatments for common and lesser-known autoimmune conditions like chronic fatigue syndrome, lupus, rheumatoid arthritis, and multiple sclerosis.

Title: b'In The Garden Of The North American Martyrs (Stories)'
Author: Tobias Wolff
Raw description: A collection of twelve short stories by Tobias Wolff. The characters include a teenage boy who tells morbid lies, a timid professor who has a genuine outburst, a prudish loner who gives a ride to an obnoxious hitchhiker, and an elderly couple on a cruise. The stories explore the characters' baffled yet resolute search for the 'right path.'

Title: b"Amelia Bedelia's Family Album"
Author: Peggy Parish, Lynn Sweat
Raw description: A children's book centered on Amelia Bedelia, the well-known literal-minded housekeeper. This story introduces the wacky and entertaining members of her equally zany family.

Title: b'De la cabeza a los pies (From Head to Toe (Spanish edition))'
Author: Eric Carle, Eric Carle
Raw description: This interactive, Spanish-language book by Eric Carle encourages young children to move their bodies. Through colorful collages of various animals, it invites kids to imitate their actions—moving heads, clapping hands, and stomping feet—helping them develop listening skills, concentration, and body control.

Title: b"Molly Moon's Incredible Book of Hypnotism"
Author: Georgia Byng
Raw description: Molly Moon, an orphan, discovers a mysterious old book on hypnotism that gives her the power to make people do whatever she wants. However, her newfound ability attracts the attention of a sinister stranger who will do anything to steal her secret.

Title: b'Walk This Way (The Autobiography of Aerosmith)'
Author: Aerosmith, Stephen Davis
Raw description: The complete and candid autobiography of the legendary rock group Aerosmith. Co-written with rock journalist Stephen Davis, the book chronicles the band's meteoric rise to fame, their struggles with drugs and excess, and their ultimate return as one of America's greatest rock bands.

Title: b'Truesight'
Author: David Stahler
Raw description: In Jacob's colony, everyone is born blind, embracing a philosophy that blindness brings unity and purity. As Jacob nears his thirteenth birthday, he begins to experience a searing pain in his eyes, threatening his future and the community's way of life. This is the first book in the Truesight trilogy.

Title: b'Living On Luck'
Author: Charles Bukowski
Raw description: A collection of letters, poems, and drawings by Charles Bukowski from the 1960s. The book showcases his characteristic blend of a rough exterior with a deeper, more complex core.

Title: b'Hell at the Breech (A Novel)'
Author: Tom Franklin
Raw description: Set in 1897 Alabama, this novel follows the aftermath of a politician's murder. His friends, poor cotton farmers, form a secret society called Hell-at-the-Breech and wage a year-long campaign of terror against those they hold responsible, culminating in a massacre. The story is told through the eyes of four people caught in the conflict.

Title: b'Hamster Champs'
Author: Stuart J. Murphy, Pedro Martin
Raw description: A children's math story where hamster champs use blocks, a board, and a protractor to measure angles and build a ramp. Their goal is to create a stunt impressive enough to outwit Hector the cat, demonstrating basic geometry concepts along the way.

Title: b'Neverwhere (A Novel)'
Author: Neil Gaiman
Raw description: Richard Mayhew, a young man with an ordinary life, is propelled into a hidden, magical world beneath London after he helps a bleeding girl. To survive this city of monsters, angels, and murderers, he must navigate its shadows and dangers to find a way back to the London he once knew.

Title: b'A Year with C. S. Lewis (Daily Readings from His Classic Works)'
Author: C. S. Lewis
Raw description: A collection of 365 daily meditations from the classic works of C. S. Lewis. Selections are drawn from his most celebrated books, including *Mere Christianity*, *The Screwtape Letters*, *The Great Divorce*, and *The Problem of Pain*, offering daily insight on themes of love, faith, and loss.

Title: b"Kenny's Window"
Author: Maurice Sendak, Maurice Sendak
Raw description: Kenny, a young boy, dreams of a fabulous, imaginary land. In his search for it, he discovers many things about himself and the process of growing up in a story that blends reality with make-believe.

Title: b'The Frog and Toad Collection Box Set (Includes 3 Favorite Frog and Toad Stories!)'
Author: Arnold Lobel, Arnold Lobel
Raw description: A slipcased collection of three classic Frog and Toad books: *Frog and Toad Are Friends*, *Frog and Toad Together*, and *Frog and Toad All Year*. The stories follow the heartwarming adventures of two best friends throughout the seasons.

Title: b'The Duke And I'
Author: Julia Quinn
Raw description: To escape the pressures of London's marriage-minded mothers, the handsome Duke of Hastings, Simon Basset, pretends to be engaged to the lovely Daphne Bridgerton. The sham courtship is meant to make Daphne more desirable to other suitors, but as they spend more time together, real feelings begin to complicate their arrangement.

Title: b'I Stink! Board Book'
Author: Kate McMullan, Jim McMullan
Raw description: A board book for young children about a garbage truck who proudly works through the night eating trash. With ten wide tires and a big appetite, he describes his job with noisy, stinky delight.

Title: b'Unlocking the Air (Stories)'
Author: Ursula K. Le Guin
Raw description: A collection of mainstream short stories by Ursula K. Le Guin that diffuses the boundaries of realism and surrealism. The tales find the strange in the everyday, exploring the unexpected depths of ordinary people with wit and a passionate sense of human frailty.

Title: b'The Compass Rose (Stories)'
Author: Ursula K. Le Guin
Raw description: A collection of twenty speculative fiction stories by Ursula K. Le Guin. The tales are organized by the points of a compass and transport the reader to worlds of wonder, horror, desire, and destiny, exploring the boundaries between reality and madness, and life and death.

Title: b"Molly's Pilgrim"
Author: Barbara Cohen
Raw description: A modern Thanksgiving classic about Molly, a young Jewish immigrant girl who feels like an outsider in her new American school. When her mother helps her with a class project by making a pilgrim doll that resembles a Russian refugee, Molly and her class learn that it takes all kinds of pilgrims to make a Thanksgiving.

Title: b'Little Critter: Snowball Soup'
Author: Mercer Mayer, Mercer Mayer
Raw description: In this 'My First I Can Read' book, Little Critter and his sister play in the snow and build a snowman. When it's time for lunch, they decide their new snowy friend must be hungry too and decide to make him a meal of 'snowball soup.'

Title: b'On Market Street 25th Anniversary Edition'
Author: Arnold Lobel, Anita Lobel
Raw description: An alphabet book and Caldecott Honor winner where a boy buys presents for a friend, with each gift corresponding to a letter. The book is known for its unique illustrations, where shopkeepers are ingeniously composed of the wares they sell, such as apples, wigs, or quilts.

Title: b'Good Omens (The Nice and Accurate Prophecies of Agnes Nutter, Witch)'
Author: Neil Gaiman, Terry Pratchett
Raw description: The classic comic novel and collaborative effort from Neil Gaiman and Terry Pratchett. It tells the story of the impending Apocalypse and the unlikely friendship between an angel and a demon who have grown fond of Earth and team up to prevent the end of the world.

Title: b'The Light Fantastic (A Discworld Novel)'
Author: Terry Pratchett
Raw description: In this second Discworld novel, the world is in danger of a disastrous collision with a star. The only person who can save it is the singularly inept wizard Rincewind, who was last seen falling off the edge of the world and must now complete his quest.

Title: b'Seekers #2: Great Bear Lake'
Author: Erin Hunter
Raw description: The second book in a thrilling animal fantasy series. Three bear cubs from different species—black, polar, and grizzly—are brought together on an epic journey. Their paths converge at Great Bear Lake, where they face danger and must fight to survive the harsh realities of the wild.

Title: b'Perfect Spy (The Incredible Double Life of Pham Xuan An, Time Magazine Reporter and Vietnamese Communist Agent)'
Author: Larry Berman
Raw description: This biography chronicles the extraordinary double life of Pham Xuan An, a *Time* magazine reporter in Saigon during the Vietnam War. While befriending American journalists, CIA agents, and South Vietnamese officials, he was secretly a master spy providing strategic intelligence to Hanoi.

Title: b'Little, Big'
Author: John Crowley
Raw description: An epic fantasy novel that follows Smoky Barnable, who travels to a mysterious, unmappable house called Edgewood to marry Daily Alice Drinkawater as prophesied. The story spans four generations of a family living on the magical border of another world, weaving a tale of love, loss, and destiny.

Title: b'Promise Not to Tell (A Novel)'
Author: Jennifer McMahon
Raw description: School nurse Kate Cypher returns to her rural Vermont home to care for her mother with Alzheimer's. When a young girl is murdered, the crime eerily mirrors the unsolved murder of Kate's childhood friend. Kate is drawn into the new investigation, forcing her to confront the grim specters of her past.

Title: b'Mac and Cheese'
Author: Sarah Weeks, Jane Manning
Raw description: An 'I Can Read' book about an odd couple of alley cats. Mac is energetic and loves to play, while Cheese is lazy and prefers to lounge. When Mac's hat blows away, the story explores whether the lethargic Cheese will spring into action to help his friend.

Title: b'Stardust'
Author: Neil Gaiman
Raw description: The provided description for this book contains only purchasing and retail information, with no summary of the plot or content.

Title: b'Collins Latin Concise Dictionary'
Author: HarperCollins Publishers
Raw description: A comprehensive reference book combining a Latin dictionary and a full grammar guide. It includes vocabulary for texts read in high school and college, detailed verb tables for regular and irregular verbs, and supplements on Roman history, life, and culture.

Title: b'Johnny Hangtime'
Author: Dan Gutman
Raw description: Thirteen-year-old Johnny Thyme is a secret movie stunt kid known as 'Johnny Hangtime.' He doubles for a teen superstar who takes all the credit. Johnny is devoted to following in his legendary stuntman father's footsteps, but faces a crisis when he is asked to perform the same dangerous stunt that killed his dad.

Title: b'Tales of the City (A Novel)'
Author: Armistead Maupin
Raw description: The first novel in the beloved San Francisco saga. It introduces a cast of characters living at the mythic apartment house at 28 Barbary Lane during the 1970s. The story began as a newspaper serial and became a sparkling comedy of manners and an indelible portrait of an era.

Title: b"Flat Stanley's Worldwide Adventures #1: The Mount Rushmore Calamity"
Author: Jeff Brown, Macky Pamintuan
Raw description: In his first worldwide adventure, Flat Stanley and his family visit Mount Rushmore. The vacation turns into a Wild West experience when Stanley and his brother team up with a scrappy cowgirl named Calamity Jasper and find themselves in a tight spot.

Title: b"Flat Stanley's Worldwide Adventures #2: The Great Egyptian Grave Robbery"
Author: Jeff Brown, Macky Pamintuan
Raw description: Flat Stanley travels by airmail to Egypt to help an archaeologist find an ancient treasure hidden deep inside a great pyramid. His unique flatness should help him navigate the tomb, but he soon finds himself in a terrible and dangerous mess.

Title: b"Flat Stanley's Worldwide Adventures #6: The African Safari Discovery"
Author: Jeff Brown, Macky Pamintuan
Raw description: When a flat skull is discovered in Africa, Stanley Lambchop travels there, hoping to find clues about his own flatness. Once there, he and his family embark on an exciting safari adventure with lions, zebras, and elephants.

Title: b'How to Paint a Dead Man (A Novel)'
Author: Sarah Hall
Raw description: A novel that weaves together the lives of four disparate characters through the prism of a still-life painting. Spanning nearly half a century and moving from Italy to England, the story is a fierce and brilliant study of art and its place in our lives.

Title: b'Danny and the Dinosaur 3-Book Box Set (Danny and the Dinosaur; Happy Birthday, Danny and the Dinosaur!; Danny and the Dinosaur Go to Camp)'
Author: Syd Hoff, Syd Hoff
Raw description: A collection of three classic 'I Can Read' stories: *Danny and the Dinosaur*, *Happy Birthday, Danny and the Dinosaur!*, and *Danny and the Dinosaur Go to Camp*. The stories follow the adventures of a young boy named Danny and his best friend, a real-life dinosaur he met at the museum.
